column10:
Killing Nazis is very satisfying, and this game doesn't fail to deliver.
Quite similar to the first one (which for me is a big plus, as I liked it a lot as well), with a couple of new features ([spoiler]contraptions, side quests, enigma machine [/spoiler] etc.).
What I liked:
- variety of locations;
- memorable characters;
- satisfying shooting and combat mechanics;
- story is alright;
- enemies are OK animation- and AI-wise;
- possibility of different playstyles and approaches (I prefer stealth, and here it's implemented nicely);
- all the fun Wolfenstein can deliver ([spoiler]riding a Panzerhund, kicking Hitler in the balls, playing Wolfenstein3D[/spoiler])
- Shoshana <3.
What I liked less:
- felt a little bit too easy comparing to the first game (especially bossfights, which are rather absent here);
- some cut scenes were a bit cringy;
- bugs (constant crashes during attempts to view a freshly found collectible, not getting an achievement about finding at least one of every collectible - those are not fixed from 2017);
TL;DR - if you liked the first game, you will like that one too, so go and shoot some Nazis ;)
